h4 Alignment
p.-text
  | Picker group text is left aligned by default. However, this behavior can change by applying the modifiers
  | <code>-align--center</code> or <code>-align--right</code>.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-pickerGroup.-fluid
        .m-picker
          input(type="radio", class="a-picker", name='box', id='id-Radio1')
          label(for='id-Radio1', class=`-align--left`) Radio1
        .m-picker
          input(type="radio", class="a-picker", name='box', id='id-Radio2')
          label(for='id-Radio2', class=`-align--center`) Radio2
        .m-picker
          input(type="radio", class="a-picker", name='box', id='id-Radio3')
          label(for='id-Radio3', class=`-align--right`) Radio3
  :code(lang='html')
    <div class="m-pickerGroup -fluid">
      <div class="m-picker">
        <input class="a-picker" type="checkbox" id="checkbox1">
        <label class="-align--left" for="checkbox1">
          Checkbox1
        </label>
      </div>
      <div class="m-picker">
        <input class="a-picker" type="checkbox" id="checkbox2">
        <label class="-align--center" for="checkbox2">
          Checkbox2
        </label>
      </div>
      <div class="m-picker">
        <input class="a-picker" type="checkbox" id="checkbox3">
        <label class="-align--right" for="checkbox3">
          Checkbox3
        </label>
      </div>
    </div>

h4 Disable Fluidity
p.-text
  | To disable the fluidity of a specific picker in a fluid picker group, apply the class <code>-notFluid</code> to the picker.

.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-pickerGroup.-fluid
        .m-picker
          input(type="radio", class="a-picker", name='box', id='ie-Radio1')
          label(for='ie-Radio1') Radio1
        .m-picker.-notFluid
          input(type="radio", class="a-picker", name='box', id='ie-Radio2')
          label(for='ie-Radio2') Radio2
        .m-picker
          input(type="radio", class="a-picker", name='box', id='ie-Radio3')
          label(for='ie-Radio3') Radio3
  :code(lang='html')
    <div class="m-pickerGroup -fluid">
      <div class="m-picker">
        <input class="a-picker" type="checkbox" id="checkbox1">
        <label for="checkbox1">
          Checkbox1
        </label>
      </div>
      <div class="m-picker -notFluid">
        <input class="a-picker" type="checkbox" id="checkbox2">
        <label for="checkbox2">
          Checkbox2
        </label>
      </div>
      <div class="m-picker">
        <input class="a-picker" type="checkbox" id="checkbox3">
        <label for="checkbox3">
          Checkbox3
        </label>
      </div>
    </div>

h3 Sizes

p.-text
  | Picker groups supports a full spectrum of sizes: <code>-sm</code>, <code>-md</code>,
  |  <code>-lg</code>, <code>-xl</code>.
  | The default size is <code>-md</code>.

.example.-mb--3
    .-px--3.-pt--0.-pb--3
      each size in ['sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl']
        p.-text--bold= '-' + size
        .-d--flex.-flex--wrap
          .m-pickerGroup
            each type in ['Radio1','Radio2','Radio3']
              .m-picker
                input(type="radio", class="a-picker", name='box', id=`if-${type}-${size}`)
                label(for=`if-${type}-${size}`, class=`-${size}`)
